description.en:
Anyone who has seen a 50 kg jackfruit on a tree in the tropics is unlikely to forget that impressive display. The fruit clusters are simply gigantic in size and also taste extraordinarily good. Due to the weight of the fruits, they must be formed directly on the stem of the tree (cauliflory). This is otherwise known from cocoa fruit, for example.
Nor do you forget the milky sap that is very difficult to wash off and can ooze out of everything. Apart from that, the jackfruit tree is also an attractive pot plant that can be kept smaller by pruning. Originally from India, jackfruit is now cultivated in all tropical countries. The jackfruit tree belongs to the Moraceae within the rose family.

Aechmea Fasciata are indoor flowering houseplants that can add great color and texture to your indoor garden. They are traditional Bromeliads, and with the Urn Plant or Silver Vase Plant being one of the most popular and well known. It has leathery tough arched leaves, blotched silver and sea green that overlap into a rosette forming a watertight "vase" or "urn" which gives rise to its common name.

Floating just above the ground, the Aetherblossom has translucent petals that shimmer with a spectral light. It grows in areas where the veil between worlds is thin, often found near ancient ruins or sites of great magical power. The flower is believed to connect the physical and ethereal realms, used in rituals to communicate with spirits.

One of the easiest of all houseplants to grow, Aglaonema is also one of the most stylish. A relatively new variety to the houseplant world, this stunner shows off dark green leaves elegantly flushed with bright red or pink. Its colorful foliage makes Red Aglaonema a perfect home-decor accent. Itâ€™s gorgeous on desks or tabletops, as well as coffee tables and side tables in dens, living rooms, and bedrooms.

A Dwarf Alocasia with glossy, dark green leaves and striking, light green to white venation as it matures. The undersides of the lanceolate leaves are a contrasting dark red/purple hue. Consistent bright, indirect light will keep this Alocasia compact and full of foliage - the more light they receive the more water and nutrients they prefer
The leaves of the Alocasia Green Dragon are ridged to perfection. Its textured foliage is matte and velvety to the touch.

From afar, it looks like Kale, but in actual reality, it is the Alocasia Low Rider. Their unique foliage is one of a kind in the Alocasia genus, making it worthy of any plant collectorâ€™s collection.

Aloe squarrosa, commonly known as the Coral Aloe, is a succulent perennial plant that features a rosette of thick, fleshy leaves. The leaves are triangular in shape and have a distinct blue-green coloration.

Aloe Vera or True Aloe is one of the most widely used medicinal plants on the planet. Itâ€™s been grown across the world for thousands of years. You need only break open the tips of its leaves to access its cooling gel for treatment of minor burns, rashes or skin irritations. Some folks even use the gel for a refreshing face mask.

Pineapple is a member of the bromeliad family (Bromeliaceae). If you want to grow and harvest pineapples yourself, you will need a lot of warmth and a little patience, especially when the fruit is ripening. Even small plants can flower and produce fruit, but these are of course much smaller than those found in the trade. Nevertheless, they exude an intense pineapple aroma as they ripen!

Ant Orchid is a mesmerizing bloom found deep within the enchanted forests of Eldoria. Thrives in shaded, moist environments, often found clinging to ancient trees or nestled among the mossy forest floorThe Ant Orchid is highly sought after for its potent magical properties. When used in potions, it can grant the drinker heightened agility and the ability to communicate with insects. It's also a key ingredient in many elixirs that promote healing and vitality.

Anthurium' Polyschistum', or Anthurium' Cochabamba'), is a rare houseplant with rippled, umbrella-like green leaves that grow well on a totem. This plant likes indirect light and consistent watering. It is perfect for those wanting a rare plant.
